        "action": "Review the fostering system to make it fairer and faster",
        "additional_details": "- How the time it takes to foster a child can be reduced\r\n- Whether additional training for staff could help ensure children are placed with good carers\r\n- How the transfer of children can be made easier.\r\n \r\nThe process is taking far too long and can take up to 18 months in some cases, which can change the minds of good carers from secure and loving backgrounds. \r\n",
        "background": "The Government should work with local authorities to review the fostering system, to consider:",
